            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Vowel harmony can significantly impact the morphology of a language, influencing how words and affixes are formed and pronounced."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "In Finnish, vowel harmony dictates that words generally contain either front vowels (like ä and ö) or back vowels (like a and o), but not both."
